      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if i use the generator, i dont have to load the whole file into a list first. but how do i actually implement that with pandas? like, do i use chunksize in the read_csv function or is there a different way to wrap the generator around the file reading so i dont accidentally create a massive object in the background?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "that makes sense. so if i use the generator, i dont have to load the whole file into a list first. but how do i actually implement that with pandas? like, do i use chunksize in the read_csv function or is there a different way to wrap the generator around the file reading so i dont accidentally create a massive object in the background?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
