    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The most direct and effective way to handle this with Pandas is by using the `chunksize` parameter in `pd.read_csv()`. When you specify a `chunksize`, Pandas doesn't return a single DataFrame; instead, it returns an *iterator* of DataFrames. You can then loop through this iterator, processing each chunk one by one before moving to the next, which keeps memory usage low. This is the built-in, optimized method for streaming large files.",
      "source": "target",
