      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This memory creep is often due to Python's garbage collection not immediately reclaiming memory from the previous DataFrame chunk. Even after you stop using it, references might linger for a while, especially if you're not explicitly detaching or deleting the variables. To combat this, ensure you are explicitly deleting the old chunk variables (`del chunk`) and forcing garbage collection (`import gc; gc.collect()`) at the end of each loop iteration.",
      "source": "target",
